    "headline": "Snap Stock Soars. AI-Related Layoffs to Gut 16% of Staff.",
    "summary": "Snap  became the latest technology company to slash its workforce this year, announcing plans Wednesday to lay off around 16% of its global full-time employees and lean into artificial intelligence.  The move is designed to streamline operations and accelerate a path to profitability, Snap said.  The social media company, which had 5,261 full-time employees at the end of 2025, will let go around 1,000 workers and close more than 300 open roles.",
